  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Buyer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary </strong><br />\nTo procure goods and services in support of company's operational requirements, ensuring cost effectiveness, compliance with quality standards, and timely delivery.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Source, identify, and evaluate suitable suppliers to meet business and operational needs.</li><li>Purchase goods and services, including negotiating commercial terms, pricing, and delivery schedules to ensure best value.</li><li>Manage and maintain strong working relationships with suppliers, including regular performance evaluation.</li><li>Analyze procurement costs and market trends to drive competitiveness and cost efficiency.</li><li>Ensure procurement activities comply with applicable regulations, internal policies, and quality standards.</li><li>Other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Business, Supply Chain Management, or a related discipline.</li><li>Minimum of 3 years of relevant working experience in procurement or a related field.</li><li>Experience working in a semiconductor manufacturing environment is required.</li><li>Proficiency in ERP systems is preferred.</li><li>Good understanding of procurement-related regulations, standards, and best practices.</li></ul>",
